## 🐛 Bug Report

**Severity:** 🔴 Critical  
**Priority:** P0  
**Platform:** Android 12+  
**App Version:** v0.4.2  
**Status:** 100% Reproducible  

---

## Summary
The mnemonic backup confirmation step can be bypassed on Android without the user entering or validating their seed phrase. The app proceeds as if the backup was successfully confirmed — no error is thrown, no block is applied. Users are left with a false sense of security, believing their wallet is backed up when it is not.

This is a **custody safety failure**, not a UX bug. A user who loses or resets their device without a valid backup will have **no recovery path** and will permanently lose access to funds.

